$ Python: string.format()
@ format

The → development/languages/Python/types/string[string] `format` method is probably what comes closest to the → development/languages/printf[printf] function of the → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/C/libc[C standard library].

gh|about-python|/types/string/format.py||

{ Left, center and right aligning strings

  Strings are left, center and right aligned with the special characters `<`, `^` and `>`:
code {
'{:<10} {:^10} {:>10}'.format('foo', 'bar, 'baz')
code }

}


